The paper deals with a mathematical problem of allocating objects to resources, which is a common topic in computer science. The use of balls-into-bins processes and occupancy problems suggests that the paper may belong to the Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) sub-category. The analysis of the maximum load and the use of random bin choices suggest that the paper may also belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. The problem of minimizing the maximum load is a classic problem in Game Theory (cs.GT), which is another possible sub-category. Finally, the use of mathematical analysis and proofs suggests that the paper may also belong to the Algorithms (cs.AL) sub-category.
